 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
WHAT SMOKES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   __ Rick DeReyes' fantasy continues. Once upon a time, the KABC
Channel 7 weatherman gave up that comfortable job to pursue a
play-by-play career for the Single-A Lancaster JetHawks. Three
years later, he's been hired by the Dodgers' Triple-A Albuquerque
affiliate for the 2000 season. ``To get there this quickly, it's
now beyond my comprehension
</P>
<P>
   I'm just overwhelmed,'' said the 43-year-old. ``The only place
tougher to get than Triple-A is the majors.'' Even if this gig
could only last a year, DeReyes has jumped at it. A group from
Portland, Ore., just bought the franchise and plans to move it to
the Northwest for 2001, at which time the Dodgers might also break
ties and try to hook up with Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
   __ Cut me, Teddy . . . and cut to commercial. On ESPN2's
``Friday Night Fights'' (tonight at 6 p.m.), trainer/analyst Teddy
Atlas plays both roles to give viewers a rare insight into what
goes into to prepping a boxer on fight night as well as in the
ring. On the card at the Blue Horizon in Philadelphia, Atlas will
do the night's first and third fights with Bob Papa at ringside,
but when Atlas leaves for the locker room to get Elviro Muriqui
ready for his six-round light-heavyweight bout, the cameras follow.
Atlas will wear a headset and mike during the fight, giving
instructions to Muriqui as well as giving viewers his insight.
``There will be a risk here . . . but I will be honest in my
assessment with my fighter and for the viewers,'' said Atlas.
</P>
<P>
   __ A classic blast in Seattle. The implosion of the Kingdome on
Sunday at 8 a.m. will have live coverage on ESPN Classic as well as
be available in glorious 3D on a Web sites called www.isee3d.com or
www.windowsmedia.com. The blue-and-red paper glasses can be used,
or there's a plug-in to download.
</P>
<P>
   __ NBC's coverage of The Players Championship plans to include,
for the first time on network TV golf coverage, global positioning
satellites to give viewers more precise yardage information on
holes 11, 13, 16 and 17. We told ya all those gizmos they use down
at the Pentagon would become useful someday. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
WHAT CHOKES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   __ Dan Marino's agent has already been peddling the former Miami
Dolphins quarterback around to the networks as a possible game
analyst. Fox and CBS have told him their broadcast rosters are full
enough of cliche-spewing, pretty-boy, recently retired gridders.
Marino's target is a package deal for ABC's ``Monday Night
Football'' with his ex-coach Jimmy Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   __ And did ya hear the one about Rush Limbaugh being on ABC's
short list of possible Al Michaels sidekicks? Neither did he until
Tomm Looney mentioned it this week on his Web site,
radiodigest.com. But at this point, ABC might was well consider
changing to a Rush-oriented game plan.
</P>
