<SLUG> BC-BBN-ELSTER-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ELSTER FIRST ON DODGERS' SHORT LIST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   VERO BEACH, Fla. _ Kevin Elster came to spring training to win a
job on the Dodgers' roster. He not only realized his goal but went
a step further: He's slated to be the starting shortstop when the
Dodgers open the season April 3 at Montreal.
</P>
<P>
   Elster, a favorite of manager Davey Johnson from their days
together with the Mets, impressed Dodgers officials enough with his
glove and bat _ despite his .233 average this spring.
</P>
<P>
   With Elster being given the starting position, it's likely Alex
Cora, given a chance to win the starting job at the start of the
spring, will be optioned to Triple-A Albuquerque.
</P>
<P>
   Manager Davey Johnson's only comment about the shortstop
situation was, ``(Elster) is playing well.''
</P>
<P>
   Because Elster, 35, was a nonroster invitee to spring training,
the Dodgers had to clear room on their 40-man roster for him.
Elster, a savvy veteran, understands the meaning of the move but
said he hasn't spoken with Johnson about his role.
</P>
<P>
   ``I still really don't know what it means, but I think it's
good,'' Elster said. ``I'm pretty excited . . . excited to play for
the Dodgers. The hard part, to me, is beginning now. We have a big,
big season to play with a lot of challenges ahead.''
</P>
<P>
   Elster hasn't dazzled this spring, but he hasn't needed to. As
he's done throughout his career, he's been steady in the field. He
has made one error while a shaky Cora has turned in some wonderful
defensive plays but committed a team-high four errors.
</P>
<P>
   Offensively, scouts say Elster has demonstrated good bat speed
and produced runs. He has one home run, six RBI and scored four
times. He's also tied for second on the team with six walks and has
a .382 on-base percentage. Johnson often talks about the value of
the No. 8 hitter prolonging an inning so the pitcher doesn't lead
off, and Elster has done that well.
</P>
<P>
   He hit .252 with 24 homers and 99 RBI with Texas in `96.
</P>
<P>
   His base salary is $300,000, but he can make an additional
$400,000 with performance-related incentives.
</P>
<P>
   ``I came in with the attitude of whatever role Davey wants me to
play, I'll play that role,'' Elster said. ``Maybe I'm a little
quick with the bat right now. I'm making good contact. There's some
days when I feel incredibly locked in. I'm very happy with the way
I feel at the plate. I thought it would take a little longer.''
</P>
<P>
   Conversely, Cora hasn't answered questions about his offense.
He's batting just .176 and has yet to drive in a run.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers also added right-handed pitcher Mike Fetters, a Van
Nuys native and Pepperdine product to the 40-man roster. To make
room for Fetters and Elster, the Dodgers designated third baseman
Kevin Orie and right-hander Dan Naulty for assignment. The Dodgers
have 10 days to trade them or risk losing them to waivers.
</P>
<P>
   ``We could have waited on that, but in all fairness to Orie and
Naulty, we had to do it now,'' Malone said. ``It gives us time to
try and find another major-league home for them. I think there's
enough interest they could be traded.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
