<P>
   MARGIN-TRADING-RISKS (Undated) _ Borrowing money to buy stocks
has become immensely popular among individual investors. And who
can blame them? When stock prices are rising, the biggest gains go
to those who buy shares on borrowed money. When stock prices are
falling, however, borrowing to buy stocks is an expensive and
highly risky business. Market regulators are growing concerned that
the recent surge in investor indebtedness, which has been greatest
at online brokerage firms, reflects the participation of many
people who do not understand how dangerous stock market debt can
be. By Gretchen Morgenson.
