<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GAYS-MILITARY (Washington) _ Saying incidents of gay harassment
are ``more widespread than I anticipated,'' Defense Secretary
William Cohen announces he will appoint a special
gays-in-the-military oversight council to combat the problem. The
Pentagon releases its inspector general's report detailing a
significant amount of verbal abuse of suspected homosexual troops
in the ranks. By ERIC ROSENBERG and STEWART M. POWELL.
(1stLd-Writethru) to story that moved earlier today.)
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday
</P>
