<P>
   VIDEO-GAMES (Undated) _ The videogame business has been
redefined in just the last month. In Japan, Sony sold nearly a
million Playstation 2 videogame consoles in the first three days on
the market. And in California, Microsoft jolted the industry with
the announcement of X-Box, a Windows PC masquerading as a videogame
console. But one should not forget the $4.2 billion industry's
greatest bit player of all: Game Boy. With nearly 88 million Game
Boys sold in the last decade, Nintendo reigns as the uncontested
heavyweight champion of selling bantamweight games you can hold in
the palm of your hand, boasting more than 99 percent of the market.
While there has been no lack of would-be rivals, the Game Boy
engenders fierce customer loyalty and has so far proven impervious
to competition. By Hutsko.
</P>
<P>
   With photo, NYT3.
