   USAIR-UNION (Undated) _ Developments in talks between US Airways
and the flight attendants as a strike deadline of midnight EST
approaches. By Steven Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   With photos, NYT1,2.
</P>
<P>
   OPEC (Vienna) _ A curtain raiser to Monday's meeting of OPEC
ministers to determine production increases and timetable. An
increase of between 1 million and 2 million barrels a day is
expected, and Saudi Arabia, the most important OPEC member, has
indicated it wants to see prices at $24 to $25 a barrel. By Edmund
L. Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stocks were up slightly in mid-afternoon.
The Dow Jones industrial average was up 7 points, the S&AMP;P 500 was 9
points and the Nasdaq 83 composite was up points. Treasury prices
were slightly lower. Crude oil was at $27.81 a barrel in early New
York trading. European stock markets were also higher: London was
up 2.10 percent and Frankfurt up 2.58 percent. The Nikkei closed up
1.29 percent; Hong Kong, up 0.42 percent.
</P>
<P>
   KRUPP-ATECS (London) _ Thyssen Krupp, the German steelmaker,
says it it is interested in acquiring Atecs Mannesmann from
Vodafone Airtouch in a transaction that could be worth as much as
$10.7 billion. An offer may cause complications for Vodafone, which
plans to sell a majority of Atec in an IPO in June. By Andrew Ross
Sorkin.
</P>
<P>
   EUROPE-BEER (Paris) _ European Union antitrust regulators raided
Heineken's offices in the Netherlands and Italy, part of a widening
investigation into possible price collusion by the world's No. 2
brewer and others. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
