   CARWASH-SLAYINGS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ William Harris said that his brother Robert,
accused of five slayings at an Irving carwash, misled him about how
the slayings happened, and now he has now idea what might have
occurred in the Mi-T-Fine Carwash. Harris had said his brother
originally told him there was a fight and he lost his temper.
Harris said he had been tormented with the idea that he could have
done more to help his brother, but that now he has given that up.
Still seeking more information on the only survivor of the
shootings, Octavio Ramos, who remains in critical condition at a
Dallas hospital. By MITCH MITCHELL and Domingo Ramirez Jr. Story
will move in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
