   FORT WORTH, Texas _ NAACP President Kweisi Mfume makes a
whirlwind trip to Fort Worth to attend a regional conference and is
expected to talk about the importance of the census, and also weigh
in on the Confederate flag plaque in Austin. (WILL BE LATE, MAY NOT
DEVELOP). By BECHETTA JACKSON. Story will move in ``a'' general
news category &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FINE-RESCINDED &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The judge who fined Burlington Northern
Santa Fe Corp. $10 million for presenting what he called ``false,
concocted'' evidence in a wrongful death trial has thrown out the
penalty and removed himself from the case. State District Judge Bob
McGrath said his sanctions were premature because they were
announced without a hearing. By LINDA P. CAMPBELL. Story will move
in ``a'' general news category.  &QL;
</P>
