   (750 words) &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MASSACHUSETTS IN HOT WATER OVER BOYCOTT. TEA, ANYONE? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MASS.-VS.-MYANMAR-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Mass. Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Call it a case of states' rights vs. nations' wrongs. Little
Massachusetts is once again standing up for the democratic values
which it so boldly asserted before the American Revolution. Then it
boycotted English imports by tossing crates of tea into Boston
Harbor. Today the state is boycotting companies which do business
with Myanmar, home of one of the world's harshest military regimes.
Alas, two lower federal courts have ruled that Massachusetts's
well-intentioned foray into foreign affairs is unconstitutional. &QL;
</P>
