   &UR; MARKET MELTDOWN: RELAX, HISTORY DOESN'T ALWAYS REPEAT ITSELF &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BOOM-TO-GLOOM?-INVESTOR-WORTH &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   There's nothing like good news for making investors nervous. As
the economy continued to grow strongly into the month of February,
it set a record for the longest economic expansion _ peacetime or
wartime _ in U.S. history. So, where does that leave investors?
Well, history shouldn't scare us. Just because the previous
long-lasting economic boom ended in economic and financial meltdown
doesn't mean that the current boom will do the same....By Jim
Jubak, ``Worth'' magazine &QL;
