<P>
   BASKETBALL/NCAA TOURNAMENT
</P>
<P>
   BKC-WOMEN-COACHES _ Of the 16 teams remaining in the NCAA
women's tournament, only four are coached by men - Georgia,
Louisiana Tech, Connecticut and Iowa State. And one of those teams
(Louisiana Tech) will lose their coach at the end of the season.
Are male coaches in women's basketball a thing of the past? Or is
it a sign that women coaches are better for the women's game?
(Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
<P>
   GOLF
</P>
