</P>
<P>
   BUSH - LITTLE ROCK, Ark. _ Presidential wannabe George W. Bush
today (Friday) brings his campaign to Little Rock, a town that
knows something about what happens when a southern governor moves
to the White House. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman). 25.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-EDUCATION _ DETROIT _ Vice President Al Gore, challenging
George W. Bush on one of the Texas governor's main reform issues,
came to this swing state Friday to hold the first of what his
campaign said would be many ``school days.'' Gore planned to spend
an entire school day among elementary students in order to
highlight his education proposals. (Shepard, Cox News Service). 20.
