   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   VETERANS _ WASHINGTON _ Promised health care for retired
military personnel is ``a moral obligation'' that must be kept,
Defense Secretary William Cohen said Friday. Cohen told reporters
at a breakfast that keeping the promise would be ``expensive,'' but
that the military was working on a plan to fund it. A class-action
lawsuit an en e-mail movement among retirees seek to force the
administration and Congress to make good on recruiters' promises to
provide free health care for life to those who made military
service a career. (Nesmith, Cox News Service). 22.
</P>
