   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   ALAMIN _ ATLANTA _ A murder indictment is expected to be
returned today against Jamil Abdullah Al-Amin from the Fulton Couty
grand jury. The story will incluse an update on the status of the
challenge to conditions in the Montgomery, Ala., jail, and talk
about steps of extradition. (Warner-Suggs, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   LEWIS-EVIDENCE _ ATLANTA _ The state is is expected to release
it's discovery evidence today _ maybe late _ against Baltimore
Ravens' All-Pro linebacker Ray Lewis. Lewis has been charged in the
double slaying of two men in Atlanta just hours after the Super
Bowl game ended. The evidence should begin painting the other side
of the story. (Rankin, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
