<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, March 25. If you
have any questions, please call The Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
SNOWCOUNT (Phoenix) - Arizona is encouraging snowbirds to list
Arizona as their home for the census. While Arizona's elders are
only considered 14 percent of the population, the same as the
national average, the number would grow to about 19 percent if all
the snowbirds were counted. That would mean more federal money for
services, and more congressional representation. But there's
competition. States like Minnesota know about the effort in Sunbelt
states like Arizona and Florida and are encouraging their snowbirds
who flock South to fill out census forms up North. By MAUREEN WEST.
Story will move in the `A` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
GASPRICES (Phoenix) - Valley drivers chalk up among the highest
miles in the nation, consuming a disproportionate amount of fuel.
So when gas prices rise, they are affected more that most.The
Arizona Republic checks to see how the recent spike in gas prices
is changing, or not changing, commuters' behaviors. By MARY JO
PITZL. Story will move in the `A` category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
