<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Saturday, March 25, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Bob Schenet on the national-foreign desk at (206)
448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   TV-HEPBURN (Undated) _ It's almost impossible to visualize the
finespun Audrey Hepburn while gazing upon the robust Jennifer Love
Hewitt. Camera tricks and acres of fabric can only do so much.
Moreover, Hewitt's spirited attempt to capture Hepburn's accent, a
challenging mix of English, Dutch and Belgian, is a persistent
obstacle to thoroughly enjoying ``The Audrey Hepburn Story,'' which
airs Monday on ABC. And yet ... And yet ... It's not so bad.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   THEATER-AIDA (New York) _ Review of Disney's Tim Rice/Elton John
``Aida,'' opening on Broadway.
