<HEADLINE>
WEST REGIONAL FINAL CAPSULE
</HEADLINE>
 REGION-CAPSULE-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
WEST REGION CAP 
No. 6 PURDUE (24-9) vs. No. 8 WISCONSIN (21-13)
<TEXT>
<P>
   PURDUE BOILERMAKERS
</P>
<P>
   COACH: Gene Keady is in his 20th season with the Boilermakers
and with a 439-190 record is Purdue's winningest coach. Though he
is well-regarded by his peers, Keady has never taken a team to the
Final Four. This would be an unlikely team to make it, but so is
Saturday's opponent, Wisconsin. Keady was named the Big Ten coach
of the year this season for the seventh time after guiding a team
picked to finish in the middle of the pack to a 12-4 record and a
third-place slot.
</P>
<P>
   KEY STATS: Defense and rebounding fuel this team. Purdue
continued its string of snuffing opposing teams that like to shoot
from beyond the arc in Thursday's semifinal victory over Gonzaga.
In three tournament games, the Boilermakers have held Dayton,
Oklahoma and the Bulldogs to nine 3-point shots in 56 attempts.
They outrebounded Gonzaga, 44-33.
</P>
<P>
   SCOUTING REPORT: Physical, physical, physical. The Boilers play
bruising basketball that isn't always pretty, but tends to wear an
opponent out.
</P>
<P>
   Will win if: They hit more 3-pointers than the Badgers. Both
play about the same around the basket and inside the line, but the
key to this game ironically may be what happens on the perimeter.
PURDUE STARTERS G JARAAN CORNELL 6-3 200 SR
</P>
<P>
   Key stats: Averages 12.6 points, 4.3 rebounds
</P>
