   F BRIAN CARDINAL 6-8 245 SR
</P>
<P>
   Key stats: Averages 14.1 points, 6.3 rebounds
</P>
<P>
   F MIKE ROBINSON 6-6 215 SR
</P>
<P>
   Key stats: Averages 11.9 points, 6.5 rebounds WISCONSIN BADGERS
</P>
<P>
   COACH: Dick Bennett, in his fifth season, is the first coach in
school history to lead the program to consecutive 20-victory
seasons. He now has the Badgers in their first regional
championship game. He seems capable of taking average players who
would battle for playing time on more talented teams and molding
them into a unit that beats those teams with marquee stars.
</P>
<P>
   KEY STATS: The Badgers held LSU to 14 first-half points in their
victory Thursday night. That's right, 14. Wisconsin doesn't shoot
well, but neither does its opponents.
</P>
<P>
   SCOUTING REPORT: This is a typical Bennett team that plays good
defense, is patient on offense and doesn't rattle by getting into
an early hole. They won two of three against the Boilermakers
during the season and just might have a slight edge in quality
depth.
</P>
<P>
   Will win if: Insiders Andy Kowske and Mark Vershaw can dominate
in the paint and their guards have a good shooting day from the
perimeter against a tenacious Purdue perimeter defense. WISCONSIN
