<P>
   (NYT23) WASHINGTON -- March 24, 2000 -- GAYS-MILITARY --
Anti-gay speech and harassment is commonplace in the U.S. military,
especially among young enlisted troops, according to a Pentagon
inspector general's survey released Friday. Deputy Under Secretary
for Planning Frank Rush pondered a question from the press during a
briefing on the results of the survey. (Susana Raab/The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- March 24, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 26 --
CAR-SMART-SUVs -- The Lexus RX300, built like a car. While most
sport utilities, including luxury models like the Cadillac Escalade
and Lincoln Navigator, have bodies fixed to truck frames,
crossovers like the Lexus RX300 and BMW X5 use one-piece unit
bodies like those found on most cars. (The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) UNDATED -- March 24, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 26 --
ABOUT-CARS-BMW-2 -- BMW would prefer that you not call the X5 an
SUV, but a ``sports activity vehicle.'' While it differs
considerably in some ways from other rugged-outside, soft-inside
vehicles, in the end it is perhaps not so different after all. (The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) UNDATED -- March 24, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 26 --
ABOUT-CARS-BMW-1 -- Responsive and plush, the BMW X5 lacks the
utility and off-road prowess of an SUV. However much the company
would like you to consider the X5 a new concept in transportation,
it walks and quacks much like a duck, er, truck. (The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) NEW YORK -- March 24, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 26 --
TROPHY-SHOPPING-3 -- A new breed of affluent fashion maven has
arrived. She is as likely to shop at off-price outlets like T.J.
Maxx, which sell designer labels, and at discounters like Target,
which produce their own wares, as she is to cruise Jeffrey or Kirna
Zabete, those outposts of downtown chic. Increasingly shrewd, such
women are driven by value, naturally - but perhaps even more by the
thrill of the chase. From J. Chuckles, a fashion hunter bagged
zebra mules ($34.99), white pants ($32), a silky black halter top
($19.99), a tailored double-breasted topper ($59) and white bag
($19.99). (Tony Cenicola/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) NEW YORK -- March 24, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 26 --
