<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROTATION ALL BUT SET
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   VERO BEACH, Fla. _ The Dodgers tentatively set their starting
rotation for the season.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Brown opens in Montreal, but Darren Dreifort won't pitch
until the club begins a three-game series in New York. Chan Ho Park
is scheduled to start the April 14 home opener.
</P>
<P>
   An announcement wasn't made, but manager Davey Johnson said,
``You can see how it's set up for the rest of spring training.''
</P>
<P>
   Brown starts the April 3 opener at Montreal and is followed by
Park, who was told two weeks ago he'd start the second game in
Montreal.
</P>
<P>
   Orel Hershiser is third and, most likely, Carlos Perez, the lone
lefty in the rotation, will finish the season-opening series.
Johnson hasn't said whether Perez or Eric Gagne will grab the final
spot in the rotation, but Perez is scheduled to start again Tuesday
in Grapefruit League action while Gagne is pitching in minor-league
games.
</P>
<P>
   Also , Perez has shown improvement lately, which Johnson wanted
to see.
</P>
<P>
   Typically, Dreifort would have earned the third spot in the
rotation based on last season and a strong spring (2-1, 2.12 ERA),
but the Dodgers want to save him for the series opener in New York
on April 7 because of the better matchup.
</P>
<P>
   Dreifort has pitched well against the Mets. He was 2-0 with a
1.26 ERA against them last season and is 2-1 with a 3.00 ERA in 13
career games.
</P>
<P>
   Though the Dodgers' 10-game season-starting road trip could
allow Brown to start the home opener, an April 10 off day before a
three-game series in San Francisco prohibits it.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not going to hold my No. 1 up if there's a day off,''
Johnson said.
</P>
<P>
   And that's not to mention Hershiser and Brown pitch well against
San Francisco, which is why they figure into each spot in the
rotation. Hershiser is 22-9 with a 3.24 ERA in 44 games against the
Giants. Brown is 7-1 with a 1.20 ERA in nine games.
</P>
<P>
   Dreifort would start the middle game of the Giants' series. Park
is slated to start the home opener against Ken Griffey Jr. and the
Cincinnati Reds.
</P>
<P>
   __ Cora surprised by move: It was expected by many but not Alex
Cora. The 24-year-old, bidding to be the Dodgers' opening- day
shortstop, was optioned to Triple-A Albuquerque early Thursday,
clearing the way for Kevin Elster to be the opening-day shortstop.
</P>
<P>
   Cora, known for his defense, led the Dodgers with four errors
and hit .176 in 34 at-bats. Barring injuries, he can't be recalled
until opening day.
</P>
<P>
   ``The last few weeks I've been playing great, especially
defensively,''Cora said. ``I think I'm back. The way I played the
last few weeks, I was a little surprised. But the way it came down,
the way I look at . . . I was on a roller coaster and I need to be
more consistent.''
</P>
<P>
   Cora could be the second young player the Dodgers expected to be
on the opening day roster who now won't be.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers said one of the reasons they traded right-hander
Ismael Valdes in the offseason was the emergence of Gagne late last
season. He went 1-1 with a 2.10 ERA in five starts, but he's
pitched miserably this spring. His 15.63 ERA landed him a start in
today's Triple-A game against the Mets and basically secured lefty
Carlos Perez's spot in the rotation.
</P>
<P>
   And though Johnson stopped short of calling Elster his starting
shortstop, that's the organization's plan, several team officials
said.
</P>
<P>
   ``He didn't do anything to lose his job as far as I'm concerned,
and he played rather brilliantly at times,'' Johnson said of Cora.
``But with the emergence of Elster and (Jose) Vizcaino, I thought
it best we don't put Alex in a part-time situation at short.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Odds and ends: Outfielder Tony Mota, son of longtime Dodgers
player and coach Manny Mota, was optioned to Triple-A Albuquerque.
. . . Shawn Green went 1 for 3 and is hitting .458 during an
eight-game hitting streak.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-24-00 2340EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
